[3] Sexual transmission of Ebola -- Part 2 of 2
Date: Tue 8 Dec 2015
Source: PLoS Blogs [edited]
http://blogs.plos.org/scicomm/2015/12/08/the-sexual-transmission-of-ebola-scicomm-as-a-matter-of-life-and-death-pt-2-of-2/


[7 weeks after Liberia was declared free from Ebola virus disease (EVD) transmission, the reemergence of EVD in Liberia in late June 2015 and November 2015 brought to center stage how the disease is transmitted, and brought the problem of sexual transmission to the forefront. The shift away from coping with a national health emergency to dealing with what may now be a "new normal" requires different public health messages for Liberians. See ProMED-mail archive 20151207.3845798 for Part 1]

